l philosophy. The idea of "logical time" is used to open up such topics as adventure, memory, imagination, and textual variation. Recent research on Troyes and on the political agency of women leads to the reappraisal of subjectivity and gender. Throughout, the medieval texts associated with the name of Chrétien are highlighted as sites where thought emerges; the implications of this thought arehistoricized and further conceptualized with the help of recent theoretical works, including those of Lacan. ZRINKA STAHULJAK, VIRGINIE GREENE, SARAH KAY, SHARON KINOSHITA and PEGGY McCRACKEN are professors at the University of California, Los Angeles, Harvard, New York University, the University of California, Santa Cruz and the University of Michigan respectively.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aFrench Studies. 4aMedieval Literature. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / French.2bisacsh  aAdventure.  aChrétien de Troyes.  aGender.  aImagination.  aIndividuality.  aLacan.  aLogical Time.  aLyric.  aMedieval Philosophy.  aMemory.  aPsychology.  aRomance.  aSocial Conditions.  aSubjectivity.1 aGreene, Virginie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKay, H S, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKay, Virginie Greene Sarah, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKinoshita, Sharon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCracken, Peggy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCracken, Sharon Kinoshita and Peggy, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aStahuljak, Zrinka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z97831114313904